          p
            | This Cookie Policy explains how 
            span.text-primary Dubbelspel Gent 
            | (“we”, “us”, or “our”) uses cookies and similar technologies to recognize you when you visit our website at 
            a(href="https://www.dubbelspelgent.be" target="_blank") https://www.dubbelspelgent.be
            | . It explains what these technologies are and why we use them, as well as your rights to control our use of them.
          p In some cases we may use cookies to collect personal information, or that becomes personal information if we combine it with other information.

          p.text-muted This cookie policy was created using Termly’s solution for cookie consent management.

          h3.mt-5 What are cookies?
          p Cookies are small data files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. They are widely used by website owners to make websites work, work more efficiently, and provide reporting information.
          p
            | Cookies set by us (Dubbelspel Gent) are called 
            em first-party cookies
            | . Cookies set by third parties are called 
            em third-party cookies
            | . They enable third-party features or functionality, such as analytics and advertising.

          h3.mt-5 Why do we use cookies?
          p We use first- and third-party cookies for several reasons. Some cookies are required for technical reasons for our website to operate (called “essential” or “strictly necessary” cookies). Others help us understand usage patterns and improve your experience. Third parties serve cookies for advertising, analytics, and other purposes.

          h3.mt-5 How can I control cookies?
          p You have the right to decide whether to accept or reject cookies. You can set your preferences in the Cookie Consent Manager, available in the banner or in your browser settings. Essential cookies cannot be rejected as they are necessary for core functionality.

          p If you choose to reject cookies, you may still use our website, though some sections may not function properly.

